4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, a court is required to
6 suspend the driver license of a person convicted of
7 eluding or attempting to elude a law enforcement
8 officer.
9 This bill would provide that a court must
10 sentence a person convicted of eluding or attempting to
11 elude a law enforcement officer to a minimum of 60 days
12 confinement.
13 This bill would also provide that a person
14 arrested for eluding or attempting to elude a law
15 enforcement officer shall not be released from jail
16 under bond or otherwise for at least 48 hours.
